The '''President of the Senate''', known also as '''President of the Galactic Senate''', or '''Senatorial Presidency''', was the official chair of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]]. In this capacity, the [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]], [[Democracy/Legends|elected]] leader of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], was vested with this title.

==History==
The title of President of the Galactic Senate was given to the [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]<ref name="visual">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> as the official leader of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]].<ref name="ROTS">{{Film|III}}</ref>

The title President of the Senate was restored and given to the [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]] of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] in their capacity as leader of the [[New Republic Senate/Legends|New Republic Senate]].<ref name="Darksaber (novel)">[[Darksaber (novel)|''Darksaber'']]</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
In [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] sources written before the [[prequel trilogy]], the term "President of the Senate" was used to refer to the head of state of the Galactic Republic; but the Prequel trilogy revealed the Republic's head of state to be called the Supreme Chancellor.  [[The Essential Chronology (real-world book)|''The Essential Chronology'']] and ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' identified the [[Sidrona|leader of the Senate]] during [[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic Qel-Droma's]] trial as President of the Senate while the [[Databank (original)|databank]] entry for Ulic Qel-Droma describes the same character as Supreme Chancellor,<ref name="db">{{DB|character|ulicqeldroma|Qel-Droma, Ulic}}</ref> [[Retroactive continuity|retconning]] "President of the Senate" to be one of the Chancellor's titles.

